body:
A QToolButton that has a menu attached (via setMenu()) and uses popupMode = QToolButton::InstantPopup is not given any dropdown/menu-indicator arrow under Kvantum. Other styles (QtCurve, Fusion) draw a small arrow to signal that the button opens a menu, so with Kvantum the user has no visual cue that the button has a menu.

With the same button set to QToolButton::MenuButtonPopup, Kvantum does draw the arrow correctly. The arrow is only missing for InstantPopup.

Steps to reproduce:
QToolButton *btn = new QToolButton;
btn->setText("Menu");
btn->setMenu(someMenu);
btn->setPopupMode(QToolButton::InstantPopup);   // no arrow under Kvantum
// btn->setPopupMode(QToolButton::MenuButtonPopup); // arrow shows

Expected: a small menu-indicator arrow is drawn (as with MenuButtonPopup and as other styles do), so it is clear the button has a menu.

Actual: no arrow is drawn for InstantPopup.

Note: I tried adding the full arrow-down element set to the theme SVG, and it had no effect, which suggests the indicator is never drawn for this case rather than being a missing SVG element.

Environment: Kvantum 1.1.2, Qt 5.15.13, Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (Noble Numbat).
